{
  "texts": [
    "Next, for each trial, we obtain w OLS using the training samples, apply WANDA to prune 30% of the weights of w OLS, and then compare the MSE loss of the unpruned and the pruned estimators on the test dataset.",
    "Our experiments involved N = 60, n = 1000, and we varied d over {20, 200, 1000}, σ over {0.2, 0.6}, and α over {0.1, 0.3}, resulting in a total of 3 × 2 × 2 experimental settings.",
    "We performed a one-sample Z-test on the mean difference between the OLS estimator loss and the WANDA pruned estimator loss and reported the pvalues.",
    "The WANDA pruned estimator consistently showed smaller MSE in the test dataset when the input features were highly correlated and irreducible error in the dataset was low.",
    "Table 4 summarizes our findings."
  ]
}